verbose_text: Nevertheless, under descriptive assessment, analysis of the present RIFLE classification results follows a similar pattern, thusly reinforcing our conclusion that, under the present experimental study conditions, the administration of cyclosporine was insufficient to prevent ischemia-reperfusion injury in rat kidneys, despite seeming to offer some degree of protective benefit as evidenced by the histological evaluation.
evidence: cyclosporine was insufficient to prevent ischemia-reperfusion injury
